snippet.textDisplay:
I think Mcgregor is in great form right now, but let’s face it. He just beat an old washed up journeyman who got shallacked out cold twice in a row before connor. Connor was looking for an easy fight. Connor and the ppl around him weren’t sure how good connor was after the huge break. So they picked the dried up Cerrone to test the waters.

Mcgregor can easily beat someone like cowboy like most others can right now. But there is no way in hell he beats Khabib, Masvidal, Ferguson, and Kamaru Usman. Connor isn’t exceptionally good in my opinion.

In connor’s rise to the top, He beat tiny guys who gas even worse than he does and those that he was easily able to get in their heads making them fight emotionally and predictably.

Mark my words, either Connor is going to look for another easy fight or he’s going to be eaten alive by any one of the aforementioned fighters.

Connor never really struck me as a guy who likes to get into wars. He seems to give up and feel beaten if the fight doesn’t go smoothly in the first couple rounds.

So i don’t think Connor is really that good. He’s more hype and a salesman that anything.
